Now it's time to talk about storage and databases.
The quiet killers.

13
01:12:00,000 --> 01:18:00,000
The costs that don't go down when you scale in.
The bills that keep growing even when you're not adding users.

14
01:18:00,000 --> 01:24:00,000
Storage and databases are different from compute.
Compute is elastic. You can scale it up and down.

15
01:24:00,000 --> 01:30:00,000
You can use Spot. You can consolidate nodes.
You can turn it off when you don't need it.

16
01:30:00,000 --> 01:36:00,000
Storage is persistent. Once you store data, it stays there.
You pay for it forever. Every month. Every byte.

17
01:36:00,000 --> 01:42:00,000
Even if no one ever looks at it again.
Even if it's a log file from three years ago.

18
01:42:00,000 --> 01:48:00,000
Even if it's a backup of a service that no longer exists.

19
01:48:00,000 --> 01:54:00,000
Databases are stateful. You can't just turn them off.
You can't just scale them down without planning.

20
01:54:00,000 --> 02:00:00,000
You have to think about data migration, connection pooling,
caching layers, read replicas, backup retention.

21
02:00:00,000 --> 02:06:00,000
You have to plan.

22
02:06:00,000 --> 02:12:00,000
But storage and databases also have huge opportunities
for savings.

23
02:12:00,000 --> 02:18:00,000
S3 lifecycle policies can automatically move old data
to cheaper tiers.

24
02:18:00,000 --> 02:24:00,000
S3 Intelligent-Tiering can do this automatically
without you writing rules.

25
02:24:00,000 --> 02:30:00,000
ECR image cleanup can delete untagged images
you're not using.

26
02:30:00,000 --> 02:36:00,000
RDS stop and start schedules can save you sixty percent
on development databases.

27
02:36:00,000 --> 02:42:00,000
RDS reserved instances can save you forty to sixty percent
on production databases.

28
02:42:00,000 --> 02:48:00,000
ElastiCache savings plans can save you on caching.
And all of this can be enforced with Terraform
so it never drifts.

29
02:48:00,000 --> 02:54:00,000
Let me tell you a story.

