127
12:36:00,000 --> 12:42:00,000
Loop through each repository.
Get the total image count, untagged image count,
total storage in gigabytes, and estimated monthly cost.

128
12:42:00,000 --> 12:48:00,000
Print the results in a table.
Sort by cost descending.

129
12:48:00,000 --> 12:54:00,000
Your top repository is your biggest waste source.

130
12:54:00,000 --> 13:00:00,000
Apply a lifecycle policy to all repositories.

131
13:00:00,000 --> 13:06:00,000
Rule one. Delete untagged images after fourteen days.

132
13:06:00,000 --> 13:12:00,000
Rule two. Keep only the last five tagged images
per feature branch, fix branch, and hotfix branch.

133
13:12:00,000 --> 13:18:00,000
Rule three. Keep only the last twenty images total.

134
13:18:00,000 --> 13:24:00,000
Lifecycle policies are evaluated at push time AND daily by AWS.
They do not run immediately when you apply them.

135
13:24:00,000 --> 13:30:00,000
The first cleanup runs within twenty-four hours.
Come back tomorrow and check your image counts.
You will typically see a sixty to eighty percent reduction.

